{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WSdfXjDDcEMMfTjybkynQP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a known MongoDB 5.0+ issue. When you add an arbiter to a replica set that has the default write concern (which is computed based on the number of data-bearing members), MongoDB complains because adding an arbiter would change the implicit default write concern.\n\nThe fix is to explicitly set `defaultWriteConcern` to `w: 1` before adding the arbiter, or to set it to the current majority. Let me set it first and then add the arbiter.\n\nActually, the exact solution is to set the cluster-wide write concern to something explicit first, typically `w: \"majority\"` or `w: 1`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":374,"cache_read_input_tokens":33239,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":374},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f81cad6-75f2-4659-98db-a0d8f24c6d73","uuid":"3a9fe0f9-fe68-4bef-bd48-2a87a6a46c21","request_id":"req_011CcMj8N5e7WGeLhT64zVqU"}
