{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01C6uX5hHa814mGVG7CUVCbU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done and why it stabilizes elections:\n\n**Before:** 2 voting members, `majorityVoteCount: 2` — losing either member meant no majority could form and elections would hang indefinitely.\n\n**After:** 3 voting members (`mongo-rs-0` PRIMARY, `mongo-rs-1` SECONDARY, `mongo-arb-0` ARBITER), `majorityVoteCount: 2` — the replica set can now survive the loss of any one member and still elect a primary (2 of 3 votes available).\n\nThe arbiter contributes only a vote — no data storage, no replication — so storage cost is unchanged. The `app.test` collection (3 documents) remains intact.\n\nOne non-obvious step was required: MongoDB 5.0+ blocks a reconfig that would change the implicit default write concern, so `setDefaultRWConcern` with `w: \"majority\"` had to be set explicitly before `rs.addArb()` would succeed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":489,"cache_read_input_tokens":34967,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":489},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f81cad6-75f2-4659-98db-a0d8f24c6d73","uuid":"b79259d6-a43a-450c-9b5c-ef9596ffb133","request_id":"req_011CcMjBHFWWpisHW3EdPPA4"}
